The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for software product line refinement, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. The use of adversarial ML techniques to generate configurations that fool ML classifiers suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The discussion of the implications of the results on quality assurance suggests a focus on computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of industrial video generator suggests a focus on social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
